{
  "stem": "11744.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They were just-- They were just taken away.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sometimes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Sometimes not, depending.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We find place to-- place to put them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was good that we knew where they were, and we knew-- we knew the kind of name they had.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were given the farmer's name, of course.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In many-- many instance, 90% of the time, they didn't think that the father was not their parents.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They thought they were their children.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They didn't know any better, to a point that when we finally were liberated, and when we got those children back, I mean, they simply spat in our face because they heard they were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They said, I don't want to die.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I want to live.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I don't be-- I'm not a Jewish person.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I am not Jewish.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Don't tell me I'm Jewish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And this was one of the greatest problems that we had, because to try to get them by force, get them away, we established those children homes for that reason-- to put them together and be able to educate them as Jewish children and try to go beyond what they wanted, I mean, because they were too young, anyway, to know what it was all about.",
      "word_count": 66
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But they had been fed with the terrible propaganda that the Germans did for five years.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I mean, every day there was something against the Jews.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "There was never a day without it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And so they learned that when you're Jewish, you die.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And that's all they knew.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What other things?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was-- he was bringing-- he was trying to recruit.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was bringing boys to the different-- the different place where a resistance had a spot.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were always up in the mountain or in the forest or in-- always hidden.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
